title: @OspreyMGolf Open Tavistock Collegiate in Tie for 6th
text: @OspreyMGolf Open Tavistock Collegiate in Tie for 6th North Florida Athletics Round 1 Results (pdf) ORLANDO -- The No. 60-ranked North Florida men's golf team carded an opening round 2-over 290 Sunday to end the day tied for sixth in the prestigious Tavistock Collegiate Invitational at Isleworth Country Club (par 72 / 7,544 yards).Freshman Philllip Knowles led the way for the Ospreys on day one firing a 1-under 71 to sit in a tie for ninth. Senior rounded out the UNF lineup with a 79 (T-68th)."The team played pretty solid today," said head coach Scott Schroeder . "This course will only give you so much so it is extremely important to stay patient. We will need to do more of the same on Monday as the wind is supposed to keep blowing and the pin locations will likely be more challenging."The 15-team field at the Tavistock is a who's who of collegiate squads featuring 13 squads currently ranked in the Top 100 highlighted by six in Top 25.No. 15 California leads the team competition after posting an opening round 279 (-9). No.26 South Carolina is second at 284 followed by No. 10 Arizona State (285), No. 3 Illinois (286) and No. 16 North Carolina (287) in the Top 5 of the team standings. Cal's Collin Morikawa tops the medalist standings after a round of 5-under 67 on Sunday.Tournament action at the Tavistock Collegiate continues with second round action Monday. North Florida tees off from Hole No. 1 beginning at 8:50 a.m. The Ospreys will be playing alongside Illlinois and North Carolina.Live scoring is available for this event online at Golfstat.com.
